This map is a remake of de_dust for CS:S, made by 3 mappers of the carpe diem mapping team : wofa2tens, Ice-Man, and Me. Why another dust map Sequel ? Mainly to improve its gameplay, by providing terrorists new ways to reach bomb sites, and giving them opportunities to attack their foes from behind if they are camping at their favorite places. Even if CTs are strong, they will no more have the map advantage, and they will have to move kickly (new corridors will allow them to move faster from one bomb site to another) to stop their opponents and defuse the bomb. But improving the gameplay has not been our only goal while doing this map : We have worked a lot on the consistency with the classical "dust look", the overall design, the indoor/outdoors sound effects, the lighting issues and of course the map performance optimization. There are 64 spawns to allow it for biggest CSS servers, but we have only tested the map performances with 25 players... You can see more preview pictures and and an overview on This site

Hi dear CS:S-Gamer, after releasing first part of CounterStrike - afterSource it´s time to show give you more. My objective was to shame the original and all remakes of de_dust! After testing map extensively by our clan "rumpelbumpel", I´ve released FINAL status. Here are some facts and figures about the map "de_dust_afterSource" : Altogether over 30 new models... 70 new textures (including all normalmaps und partially specularmaps) but basically the same play expiry as it is known in the original map! In the screenshot gallery you can get some impressions of the map and selected models! If you want to get an idea of the realism and the game expiry, download and play the map! VERY IMPORTANT: You have to turn on the color correction in the option menu, under graphics. The map has a color correction entity, which brings up the real athmosphere! Credits: Special thanks to my Wingman Stubu, which spend a lot of time with testing the project and to for creating an awesome professional NAV-file! Further thanks to: Herr Freimann, DA_KILLA, Muckel, Ibex, Richie, Rambob, Saxil and the whole rumpelbumpel´s! Yours rumpelbumpel visit us at our homepage: www.rumpelbumpel.de

This is a small-medium defuse map with a single bomb spot. The layout is roughly based on a plain looking, little known map from 10 years ago called de_dust_small. I did make quite significant layout changes by adding a bunch of new pathways including an underground section and also improved the aesthetics a lot. But I still kept the name to honour the work of the original creator.

Heres a link to the original map

https://gamebanana.com/maps/99960

While the map didn’t look like much I quite liked the unique gameplay that plays somewhat similar to csgos new retake mode. 

On this map the Ts start closer to the bombspot than the CTs and are virtually guaranteed to be able plant the bomb (if they rush). Its then on the CTs to find a way to retake the spot. As you can see from the overview there are roughly 4-5 different routes the CTS can take and the Ts have to defend – as to not make it too easy for the Ts. The bomb timer is also extended to 50s to make time a little issue for the CTs. Its more about skill , positioning and tactics.

Given the 4-5 different paths which can each easily hold 2-3 player from each team the map is best played with more than 12  players for the full potential but the map is also small enough to play some fast paced 1v1s or 2v2s if you like – although I suspect the retake aspect will be off little importance then.

Have fun

PS: dont go all forensic on me about the visual style ; ) I know the map is not really culturally accurate. Its more a blend of different asian cultures and building style that I created mostly off the top of my head.
